  "response": "Here are some interesting places to visit en route from Chennai to Pondicherry:\n\n1. Mahabalipuram (45 km from Chennai)\n- UNESCO World Heritage Site\n- Shore Temple\n- Five Rathas\n- Krishna's Butter Ball\n- Rock-cut sculptures\n\n2. Cholamandal Artists' Village (near Chennai)\n- Art museum\n- Artists' workshops\n- Sculpture park\n\n3. Kanchipuram (75 km from Chennai)\n- Famous temple city\n- Ekambareswarar Temple\n- Kailasanathar Temple\n- Silk saree shopping\n\n4. Alamparai Fort (near ECR)\n- Historic coastal fort\n- Scenic backwaters\n- Photography opportunities\n\n5. Muttukadu Boat House\n- Water sports\n- Boating\n- Picnic spot\n\n6. Kovalam Beach\n- Scenic coastal area\n- Beach activities\n- Lighthouse\n\n7. Crocodile Bank (near Mahabalipuram)\n- Reptile conservation center\n- Variety of crocodile species\n- Educational experience\n\n8. Dakshinachitra Museum\n- Cultural heritage museum\n- Traditional architecture\n- Craft demonstrations\n\nThese places offer diverse experiences and are conveniently located along the Chennai-Pondicherry route.",
